#: src/providers/overview.md:1
msgid "Model Providers — Overview"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:3
msgid ""
"Model providers are ZeroClaw's abstraction over any LLM endpoint the agent "
"can call. Every chat-completion request goes through a `Provider` trait "
"implementation (`zeroclaw-api::Provider`), whether the target is a remote "
"API, a self-hosted inference server, or a local Ollama model."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:5
msgid ""
"Why \"model\" provider? We use the phrase \"model provider\" consistently — "
"there may be other kinds of providers in the future (memory providers, tool "
"providers, etc.) and keeping the word specific avoids ambiguity."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:7
msgid "Supported providers"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:9
msgid "Three categories:"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:11 src/providers/catalog.md:9
msgid "Native"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:13
msgid "One-off implementations that talk to a provider's native API:"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:15
msgid ""
"**Anthropic** — Claude models. Supports OAuth (`sk-ant-oat*`) and API keys."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:16
msgid "**OpenAI** — GPT and o-series models."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:17
msgid ""
"**Ollama** — local inference. Native `/api/chat` endpoint with schema-based "
"structured output."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:18
msgid ""
"**Bedrock** — AWS foundation models (Claude, Llama, Titan, etc.). IAM-"
"authenticated."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:19
msgid ""
"**Gemini** — Google's API. Separate `gemini_cli` provider for CLI-based auth."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:20
msgid "**Azure OpenAI** — Microsoft's Azure-hosted OpenAI endpoint."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:21
msgid "**Copilot** — GitHub Copilot as a chat model. OAuth flow built in."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:22
msgid ""
"**Claude Code** — Anthropic MCP proxy that lets the agent delegate to a "
"Claude Code session."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:23
msgid "**Telnyx** — voice AI over Telnyx's platform."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:24
msgid "**KiloCLI** — local inference via KiloCLI."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:26
msgid "OpenAI-compatible (single implementation, 20+ endpoints)"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:28
msgid ""
"One Rust implementation (`compatible.rs`) handles every OpenAI-compatible "
"endpoint. A partial list:"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:30
msgid "Groq, Mistral, xAI, DeepSeek"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:31
msgid ""
"OpenRouter (also exposes provider-routing semantics — see [Fallback & "
"routing](./fallback-and-routing.md))"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:32
msgid "Venice, Moonshot, Synthetic, OpenCode, Z.AI, GLM, MiniMax, Qianfan"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:33
msgid "Vercel Gateway, Cloudflare Gateway"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:34
msgid ""
"Any SaaS or self-hosted endpoint that speaks OpenAI's chat-completions API"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:36
msgid ""
"To add one of these, you don't implement a new provider — you add a config "
"entry pointing at its base URL."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:38
msgid "Meta providers"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:40
msgid ""
"**`reliable`** — wraps any provider with a fallback chain. First failure "
"falls to the next provider in the list."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:41
msgid ""
"**`router`** — a multi-provider router that picks a backend based on per-"
"request hints (`hint:reasoning`, `hint:cheap`, `hint:vision`, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:43
msgid "Configuration shape"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:45
msgid "Every provider is configured under `[providers.models.<name>]`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:47
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[providers.models.claude]\n"
"kind = \"anthropic\"\n"
"model = \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\"\n"
"api_key = \"sk-ant-...\"\n"
"\n"
"[providers.models.local]\n"
"kind = \"ollama\"\n"
"base_url = \"http://localhost:11434\"\n"
"model = \"qwen3.6:35b-a3b\"\n"
"\n"
"[providers.models.groq]\n"
"kind = \"openai-compatible\"\n"
"base_url = \"https://api.groq.com/openai\"\n"
"model = \"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\"\n"
"api_key = \"gsk_...\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:65
msgid "See [Configuration](./configuration.md) for the full schema."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:67
msgid "Selecting a provider"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:69
msgid "Two mechanisms:"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:71
msgid ""
"**`default_model`** in the top-level config picks which provider the agent "
"loop uses by default."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:72
msgid ""
"**Channels and tools can override.** A channel config can specify `provider "
"= \"claude\"` to use Claude for that channel's responses while "
"`default_model` stays set to a cheaper option for the rest."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:74
msgid "Why provider-agnostic matters"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:76
msgid "Two practical reasons:"
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:78
msgid ""
"**Vendor lock-in is a liability.** If OpenAI changes their pricing, "
"throttles you, or deprecates a model, you swap `kind = \"openai\"` for `kind "
"= \"anthropic\"` in one file. The rest of the system doesn't care."
msgstr ""

#: src/providers/overview.md:79
msgid ""
"**Cost/performance routing.** A fallback chain of `[sonnet, haiku, local]` "
"means you use the best model when it's available, fall back to cheaper "
"hosted when it's not, and keep running on local Ollama during an API outage."
msgstr ""

