#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:1
msgid "Tool Receipts"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:3
msgid ""
"Tool receipts are cryptographic proofs that a tool actually ran. Every tool "
"invocation — approved, blocked, or auto-approved — produces an HMAC-SHA256 "
"digest over the call and its result. The digest is appended to the tool-"
"result text and passed back to the model as part of the conversation."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:5
msgid ""
"The practical outcome: the model cannot claim to have run a tool it didn't "
"run, and it cannot fabricate a tool result. Both produce receipt mismatches "
"the runtime detects."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:7
msgid "The threat model"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:9
msgid ""
"An LLM is a string generator. By default, nothing prevents it from narrating "
"a tool call it never made (\"I ran `git log` and the latest commit is…\"), "
"or inventing a result for a tool call (\"The weather API says 72°F\" — when "
"the call timed out). For an agent with autonomy, this is more than a "
"correctness issue — it's a deniability issue."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:11
msgid ""
"Tool receipts close that gap with the cheapest possible construct: a "
"symmetric MAC with an ephemeral per-session key."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:13
msgid ""
"Based on: Basu, A. (2026). \"Tool Receipts, Not Zero-Knowledge Proofs: "
"Practical Hallucination Detection for AI Agents.\" [arXiv:2603.10060]"
"(https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2603.10060)."
msgstr ""
"出典: Basu, A. (2026). \"Tool Receipts, Not Zero-Knowledge Proofs: Practical "
"Hallucination Detection for AI Agents.\" [arXiv:2603.10060](https://doi.org/"
"10.48550/arXiv.2603.10060)。"

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:15
msgid "How it works"
msgstr "動作方法"

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:17
msgid ""
"At agent-loop startup, a 256-bit key is generated. It's ephemeral — never "
"written to disk, never sent to the model, never logged."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:18
msgid "After each tool invocation, the runtime computes:"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:22
msgid "The receipt is appended to the tool-result text as:"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:26
msgid "The tool result (with the receipt) is fed back to the model."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:28
msgid ""
"The model sees every receipt in its conversation history. It can echo them "
"in text it produces to the user. But it cannot produce a _new_ valid receipt "
"— the HMAC requires the session key, which the model doesn't have."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:30
msgid "Receipt shape"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:37
msgid ""
"The `zc-receipt-` prefix exists so the leak detector doesn't redact them "
"(receipts are safe to surface; they contain no secret material)."
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:39
msgid "What receipts detect"
msgstr "領収書が検出するもの"

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:41
msgid "Scenario"
msgstr "シナリオ"

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:41
msgid "Without receipts"
msgstr "領収書なし"

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:41
msgid "With receipts"
msgstr "領収書あり"

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:43
msgid "Model claims it ran a tool, didn't"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:43 src/security/tool-receipts.md:44
msgid "Undetectable"
msgstr "検出不可能"

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:43
msgid "No receipt — fabrication visible"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:44
msgid "Model fabricates a result for a real call"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:44
msgid "HMAC mismatches on verification"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:45
msgid "Model denies a call it did make"
msgstr ""

#: src/security/tool-receipts.md:45
msgid "Unverifiable"
msgstr "検証不可能"

