#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:32
msgid "1. The Documentation Philosophy"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:34
msgid ""
"Documentation problems almost always come from skipping a question that "
"should have been asked before writing the first sentence: **what kind of "
"document is this, and who is it for?**"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:36
msgid ""
"Without an answer to that question, documentation accumulates as a pile of "
"pages that are all slightly different shapes of the same vague category: "
"\"stuff about the project.\" Setup guides live next to architecture "
"decisions. User-facing how-tos sit alongside internal coding standards. "
"Thirty language translations of the README compete for space with the single "
"security policy document. Nobody can find anything, everything goes stale at "
"a different rate, and every PR that touches documentation becomes a "
"negotiation about which pages need updating."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:38
msgid ""
"The fix is not to write more documentation. The fix is to decide, before "
"writing anything, what type of artifact you are creating. Type determines "
"format, audience, location, lifecycle, and who is responsible for keeping it "
"current. Once type is established, the rest follows naturally."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:40
msgid ""
"This RFC adopts the **EA Artifacts on a Page** framework by Svyatoslav "
"Kotusev (https://eaonapage.com) as the classification lens for all ZeroClaw "
"documentation. The framework is evidence-based, deliberately non-"
"prescriptive, and maps directly onto the kinds of documents an open source "
"infrastructure project actually needs."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:42
msgid ""
"The core principle, borrowed from the broader development philosophy this "
"team is adopting:"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:44
msgid ""
"**Documents, like code, should trace a line upward through Vision → "
"Architecture → Design → Implementation. If you cannot name the artifact type "
"and its audience before writing, you are not ready to write.**"
msgstr ""

