#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:247
msgid "6. ADR Standards"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:249
msgid "6.1 The Format"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:251
msgid ""
"All Architecture Decision Records use the **Nygard format**, extended with "
"YAML frontmatter for machine readability. ADR-004 is the existing model — "
"this section formalizes it."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:253
msgid "Every ADR has three sections and five frontmatter fields:"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:255
msgid ""
"```\n"
"---\n"
"id: ADR-NNN\n"
"title: Short imperative sentence describing the decision\n"
"date: YYYY-MM-DD\n"
"status: proposed | accepted | deprecated | superseded-by-ADR-NNN\n"
"relates-to:\n"
"  - ADR-XXX (optional, list of related decisions)\n"
"  - crates/zeroclaw-api (optional, affected code paths)\n"
"---\n"
"\n"
"# ADR-NNN: Title\n"
"\n"
"## Context\n"
"\n"
"What is the situation, constraint, or problem that required a decision?\n"
"What forces were at play? What options were considered?\n"
"\n"
"## Decision\n"
"\n"
"What was decided? State it in the active voice.\n"
"\"We will...\" not \"It was decided that...\"\n"
"\n"
"## Consequences\n"
"\n"
"What are the results of this decision?\n"
"List both positive consequences and negative ones — every decision has "
"tradeoffs.\n"
"Note any follow-up decisions or actions this creates.\n"
"\n"
"## References\n"
"\n"
"Links to the relevant code files, issues, and external resources.\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:289
msgid "6.2 ADR Lifecycle Rules"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:291
msgid ""
"**ADRs are immutable once accepted.** If a decision changes, the old ADR is "
"marked `superseded-by-ADR-NNN` and a new ADR is written describing the new "
"decision and why it superseded the old one."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:292
msgid ""
"**ADRs are numbered sequentially and never renumbered.** Gaps in the "
"sequence are acceptable (a proposed ADR that was rejected can be withdrawn, "
"leaving a gap)."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:293
msgid ""
"**ADRs live in `docs/architecture/decisions/`.** They are named `ADR-NNN-"
"short-slug.md`."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md:294
msgid ""
"**Significant architectural changes require an ADR.** \"Significant\" means: "
"a decision that would be surprising to a new contributor, a decision that "
"constrains future choices, or a decision that involves a non-obvious "
"tradeoff."
msgstr ""

