#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:939
msgid "11.2 GitHub Actions Workflows"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:941
msgid ""
"**Auto-label by changed files (`.github/workflows/label-by-path.yml`):**"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:943
msgid ""
"Automatically add component and risk labels to PRs based on which files were "
"changed. A PR touching `src/security/` gets `component:security` and "
"`risk:high`. A PR touching `docs/` gets `type:docs` and `risk:low`. This "
"eliminates the requirement for PR authors to remember to label their own PRs "
"and gives reviewers immediate context."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:945
msgid ""
"**Auto-request CODEOWNERS review (built into CODEOWNERS — no Action "
"needed):**"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:947
msgid ""
"GitHub enforces CODEOWNERS automatically when the file exists and branch "
"protection requires it. No Action required."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:949
msgid "**Stale issue management (`.github/workflows/stale.yml`):**"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:951
msgid ""
"Issues with no activity for 45 days are labeled `status:stale` and a comment "
"is posted asking if the issue is still relevant. Issues with no activity for "
"15 days after the stale label is applied are closed. This prevents the "
"backlog from accumulating hundreds of issues that are months old and no "
"longer relevant. Exclude `status:blocked`, `priority:critical`, and "
"`type:rfc` from the stale process."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:953
msgid "**PR size labeling (`.github/workflows/pr-size.yml`):**"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:955
msgid ""
"Automatically label PRs with `size:xs` through `size:xl` based on lines "
"changed. This gives reviewers and maintainers an immediate sense of scope "
"without opening the diff. Use these thresholds as a starting point: XS \\< "
"10 lines, S \\< 50, M \\< 250, L \\< 1000, XL ≥ 1000."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:957
msgid ""
"**Milestone check on PR merge (`.github/workflows/milestone-check.yml`):**"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:959
msgid ""
"Warn (not block) if a PR is merged without a linked issue that has a "
"milestone assigned. This is a gentle nudge, not a hard gate — the goal is to "
"prevent work from happening without being tracked to a release."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:961
msgid "11.3 What NOT to Automate Yet"
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:963
msgid ""
"**Automated release drafts:** GitHub's release-drafter is useful but adds "
"configuration overhead. Add it after the team has established a stable "
"release rhythm."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:964
msgid ""
"**Automated dependency updates (Dependabot PRs):** Enable Dependabot "
"security updates (free, low noise), but defer automated version bumps until "
"the team has CI stability. Bumping versions creates noise before the CI "
"foundation is solid."
msgstr ""

#: src/foundations/fnd-003-governance.md:965
msgid ""
"**Sprint planning automation:** Do not automate sprint planning. It requires "
"human judgment about capacity, priority, and team context that no automation "
"can replace at this team size."
msgstr ""

